    <body class="community-enabled">
        <h1> Download, Install and Sign in to the Royo Dispatcher App</h1>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In this article, you will learn how to begin using the Royo Dispatcher App. Check out the Driver Quick Start Guide at the bottom for a high-level look at using the Royo Dispatcher mobile app.</span></p>
        <h1 id="h_01EM2AHV124SRJR7E6R38X2GMY"><span class="wysiwyg-underline"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Signing up</span></span></h1>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Access to the Royo Dispatcher mobile app is by invitation only.&nbsp;</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A company that uses Royo Dispatcher must first add you as a driver before you can log in. A company here refers to an employer of drivers that provide driver screening, orientation, payroll information (paychecks &amp; earnings), and support to all other driver operations. Contact your dispatcher team directly when you need access to these before mentioned information.</span></p>
        <h1><span class="wysiwyg-underline"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Royo Dispatcher App&nbsp;</span></span></h1>
        <p data-renderer-start-pos="330"><span data-renderer-mark="true">Once you have been invited by your organization to join Royo Dispatcher, you will receive an SMS message with a download link </span><span data-renderer-mark="true">and a company code. Tap the link to be taken to the App or Play Store page where you may download the Royo Dispatcher app. You will need the company code from the SMS message to log in for the first time. Afterward, you will be asked to enter your mobile number.</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-> Make sure your mobile number is registered by dispachter compnay as driver. </span></p>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-> Then driver needs to tap Log In. </span></p>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-> Upon tapping Log In, you will receive an SMS with a OTP. </span></p>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-> Enter the OTP in OTP screen received through SMS. </span></p>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-> If didn't receive the OTP try resend OTP option or contact your dispatcher. </span></p>
        <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-> Lastly, by tapping Log In you should successfully be logged in and see the standard off duty screen. </span></p>
